Actress Funke Akindele’s ex-hubby Abdulrasheed Bello aka JJCSkillz has reportedly remarried barely eight months after their separation.  The rapper and record producer allegedly married an indigene of Kogi State Falilat Raji in a secret ceremony. It was also gathered that Bello declined to be captured on camera in the wedding ceremony that took place last month in Kano State. The Peoples Democratic Party Lagos Deputy Governorship candidate and the father of their twins broke up on June 30, 2022. JJC Skillz announced the end of the union which lasted six years via his official Instagram handle. In the post, JJC said he tried to save the marriage through amicable resolution but was unsuccessful. He also revealed that the Jenifa star threw him out of their home inside AMEN estate, Lagos. Seven months after, Bello expressed gladness to have embraced Islam again after practicing Christianity from his teen years.